Outstanding breakfast and lunch joint with fast, casual atmosphere and fresh, delicious, made to order dishes.  The salmon scramble and Greek Omelette were outstanding, and if you enjoy coffee, try their house blend with a hint of mocha. You won’t be disappointed. On top of great food, the staff is friendly and fairly quick. It’s a hole in the wall that’s definitely worth the stop.

We used to love this place and would frequent once a month or so. A couple of years ago they changed management and it immediately went downhill in every respect except for the house coffee (which remains excellent).  We’ve tried it a few times since the new management took over and it has unfortunately not improved. The quality of the  food is worse than a below average greasy spoon diner, the portions are measly, and the prices have increased significantly.  Again - the only thing that remains its excellent same is the house coffee.  It makes me sad to write this. I hope they change management again, because this neighborhood needs a place like Made Fresh Daily.

Missing food & Can't even get a refund on the spot!  Ordered Bagel with Lox and Frittata of The Day for pick up. We were in a rush but we noticed there was no Frittata included. We spoke with the waitress, and we even had to show her the payment and order confirmation (since she made it as if we were lying and trying to steal that stupid frittata). Anyway, she finally said we had to wait for 10 minutes but we couldn't. So she told us to write down our name and telephone so the manager could issue us a refund. Guess what? We never got the damn call, and of course we didn't get the refund.  I guess I will have to dispute that stupid $12 plus tax with my credit card company. What makes me mad the most is there wasn't any apologies by the waitress. I get it...you were busy, and we were just picking up order with no tips. But seriously? How could it be my fault?! We are all humans, and we all make mistakes. It is about how you handle the situation and not blaming on others.  Such a shame.

Went there this morning for a to-go order. Everything is made to order (very nice). The ham, egg, and cheddar biscuit was good (hubby liked it). The vegetarian eggs were tasty, veggies not over cooked, and the perfect amount of seasoning. The toast with the eggs was stale :-/. There is no flavoring for coffee m. A pump of vanilla would have been nice and I’d have even paid extra for it. It’s very easy (and cheap) to make vanilla syrup. Or, offer a shot of real maple syrup for the coffee since you have that on hand? The person taking the order was friendly enough but chucked when I asked what the soup of the day was at 8:30am. I like soup all day. I guess I’m weird lol. I’ll try it again since it’s 5 minutes away...
